sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Returns an event.

Inputs:

  • Calendar ID - Calendar identifier ID. If you want to access the primary calendar of the currently logged in user, use the "primary" keyword.
  • Event ID - Event identifier ID.

Outputs:

  • Event - Event is an object. It has event resource information. Read More
    • Event ID - Event identifier ID.
    • iCal UID - Event unique identifier as defined in RFC5545 (Note that the I Cal UID and the Event ID are not identical).
    • HTML Link - An absolute link to this event in the Google Calendar Web UI.
    • Summary - Title of the event.
    • Description - Description of the event.
    • Location - Geographic location of the event as free-form text.
    • Hangouts Meeting Link - An absolute link to the Hangouts Meeting associated with this event.
    • Created - Creation time of the event (as a RFC3339 timestamp).
    • Updated - Last modification time of the event (as a RFC3339 timestamp).
    • Start Date - The (inclusive) start time of the event.
      • Start Date Time - The time, as a combined date-time value (formatted according to RFC3339).
      • Time Zone - The time zone in which the time is specified.
    • End Date - The (exclusive) end time of the event.
      • End Date Time - The time, as a combined date-time value (formatted according to RFC3339).
      • Time Zone - The time zone in which the time is specified.
    • Organizer - The organizer of the event.
      • Email - The organizer's email address, if available. It must be a valid email address as per RFC5322.
      • Self - Whether the organizer corresponds to the calendar on which this copy of the event appears. The default is false.
    • Attendees - The attendees of the event.
      • Email - The attendee's email address, if available. This field must be present when adding an attendee. It must be a valid email address as per RFC5322.
      • Response Status - The attendee's response status.
    • Conference Data - Conference details.
      • Entry Point Type - Information about individual conference entry points, such as URLs or phone numbers.
      • URI - The URI of the entry point.
      • Label - The label for the URI.
      • Pin - The PIN to access the conference.
      • Meeting Code - The meeting code to access the conference.
      • Passcode - The passcode to access the conference.
      • Password - The password to access the conference.
  • Status - Will be set to “Success" if the request succeeds or “Error" if there is a failure while getting an event.
  • Error Message - Description of the error occurred. Populated when the error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • The specified resource was not found (when the requested resource (with the Calendar ID) has never existed or when accessing a calendar that the user cannot access).
  • The user has reached Google Calendar API's maximum request rate per calendar or per authenticated user.
  • Invalid authorization header. The access token you're using is either expired or invalid.

To use this action, the corresponding Google Calendar connection and credential must be created and associated with the Google Calendar Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More
